## 🚀 Firebase Hosting Setup

I have configured the project for **Static Export**. To deploy your project to Firebase Hosting, follow these steps:

### 1. Build the Project
Run the building command to generate the static files:
```bash
npm run build
```
This will create an [out](file:///C:/Users/sarbr/Desktop/Antigravity/Projects/SustainaBuy_v0.2/contexts/AuthContext.tsx#27-28) folder in your project root.

### 2. Initialize Firebase (if not done)
If you haven't initialized hosting yet, run:
```bash
firebase init hosting
```
- **What is your public directory?** Enter [out](file:///C:/Users/sarbr/Desktop/Antigravity/Projects/SustainaBuy_v0.2/contexts/AuthContext.tsx#27-28).
- **Configure as a single-page app?** No (because we are using static export).
- **Set up automatic builds/deploys with GitHub?** Optional.

### 3. Deploy
Once ready, simply run:
```bash
firebase deploy --only hosting
```

